column1: #Text=The remains were mostly skeletonized and the estimated time of death was months before , perhaps as early as Autumn of 1978 . [ 4 ] [ 7 ]
#Text=The decedent is believed to have been between 15 and 30 years old , although she may have been as old as 38 . [ 4 ]
#Text=She was white , had straight , shoulder-length blond or light brown hair and was between 5 feet 2 inches and 5 feet 9 inches tall . [ 3 ] [ 7 ]
#Text=She had received dental care during her life , as a back tooth had been removed four or five years prior to her death .
#Text=She also had teeth fillings .
#Text=One tooth , which was a molar , had not yet erupted . [ 7 ]
#Text=Her teeth showed no evidence of crowding .
#Text=Despite that her teeth appeared to have had some dental work , it is not known if she had ever had braces . [ 2 ]
#Text=Prior to her death , she had suffered a fractured rib , which had healed . [ 6 ]
#Text=Just before her death , she may have returned to Pennsylvania after having spent several months in the southwestern United States . [ 8 ]
#Text=Recent analysis of the decedent 's bones indicated that she had spent a long time living in the Midwest or in Canada , near the Great Lakes , when she was an adolescent . [ 6 ]
#Text=Belongings
#Text=Jewelry worn by Perry County Jane Doe .
#Text=Perry County Jane Doe wore several pieces of jewelry .

#Text=She was wearing two sterling silver rings with turquoise stones , one of which also contained onyx pieces that are believed to have originated in the Southwest , possibly having been made by Navajo or Zuni Indians inhabiting that area . [ 9 ]
#Text=She also had a chain bracelet on her right arm and a turquoise necklace and earrings . [ 2 ] [ 6 ]
#Text=The jewelry led authorities to believe the victim had ties to Arizona , New Mexico or a similar region . [ 1 ]
#Text=She wore a tan jacket , white boots with silver buckles , green and white socks , and blue slacks . [ 10 ]
#Text=The slacks were described as having been made from knitted wool which contained strands of red thread . [ 2 ]
#Text=She was wearing two tops , which consisted of a white shirt and a blue tank top . [ 2 ] [ 4 ]
#Text=Investigation
#Text=The victim had been buried shortly after her discovery , but was exhumed in 2008 , following the reopening of her case . [ 1 ]
#Text=Her DNA and dental records were recorded and are on file .
#Text=Because of the condition of her remains , no fingerprints and no cause of death could be confirmed . [ 4 ]
#Text=An initial examination of her teeth indicated that she had had three teeth extracted , but this was later disproved . [ 2 ] [ 4 ] [ 7 ]
#Text=Despite the fact that these characteristics have been entered into national databases , there have been no matches with missing persons . [ 1 ]
#Text=About sixty possible identities for her have been ruled out . [ 3 ]
#Text=Her face was reconstructed twice by professionals .

#Text=A sketch by Barbara Martin-Bailey was drawn in 2009 , and the National Center for Missing and Exploited Children created a three-dimensional rendering by digitally adding layers of muscles and skin to a CT scan of her skull , which was released in 2013 .
#Text=A revised image was later released in 2018 . [ 6 ]
